benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/healthcheck - Put the host out of rotation

covered: Valid Deletion: 204 on success and host status updated to out of rotation
Server error handling: 500 for internal errors during operation
Invalid HTTP method: 405 (e.g., GET instead of DELETE)
Extra parameters: 204 with extra query parameters
Malicious payload and header injection: 400 for invalid request body or headers
Performance: 204 within 1 second under normal load
Performance: concurrency handling: first response 204, others 204/409 as appropriate within 2 seconds
Edge Case: No hosts in rotation: 409 for no available hosts
Regression: Reconfirmation that host is out of rotation after DELETE (204, and status check)
Query after operation: status query confirms host is out of rotation
Security headers injection: test coverage for malicious header values
gaps: Comprehensive parameter validation beyond extra parameters not fully covered
Large/payload edge cases for DELETE body not applicable or not tested beyond malicious payload
recommendations: Add a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions, in addition to 401 cases
Add explicit 404 Not Found / Non-Existent Resource test (or clarify 409 semantics for no hosts)
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under high load
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) if applicable
Add broader parameter-validation tests (a variety of invalid/edge-case parameters beyond extra query params)
Include a soft-delete semantics check if the domain model supports soft deletion (e.g., ensuring the host is marked out but not removed)
Expand header-security tests beyond malicious values to cover other injection vectors and malformed headers
